{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πένομαι</b>, <br /> used only in <i>present</i> and <i>imperfect</i>, (compare πενέω): <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <i>intransitive</i>, <b>toil, work</b>, ἀμφίπολοι.., ἐνὶ μεγάροισι πένοντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.348 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; περὶ δεῖπνον ἐνὶ μεγάροισι π. <b>were busy</b> preparing a meal,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.624; ἀμφ᾽ αὐτὸν ἑταῖροι ἐσσυμένως ἐπένοντο 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.124. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> after [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], (<b>to have to work for one's living</b>, hence) <b>to be poor</b> or <b>needy</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Solon Lyricus 15, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 1220, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.40, etc.; πλουσία ἢ πενομένη πόλις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 577e \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; πλουτοῦντες ἢ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Plt.” 293a; π. καὶ κάμνειν [prev. author] “Grg.” 477d. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> with <i>genitive</i>, <b>to be poor in, have need of</b>, τῶν σοφῶν (i. e. τῆς σοφίας) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 431; ὡς διαλλαγὰς ἔχοιμεν ἀλλήλοισιν ὧν πένοιτο γῆ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 210; πάντων 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “ad Marcellam - Porphyrii Opuscula” 27; πενόμενον τὴν ψυχὴν τῶν ἐπιβαλλόντων αὐτῇ καλῶν 5th c.AD: Hierocles Platonicus Philosophus “in Carmen Aureum - FPG” 14p.451M.: with _accusative_, χρήματα 4th c.AD: Themistius Sophista “Or.” \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>](i. e. Constant.<b>pro Them.</b>) 22b. <br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>transitive</i>, <b>work at, get ready</b>, δόμον κάτα δαῖτα πένοντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.322, compare 3.428, etc.; ἔργα 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 773 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὁππότε κεν δὴ ταῦτα πενώμεθα when we <b>are a-doing</b> this, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.394 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τί σε χρὴ ταῦτα πένεσθαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"; 24.407, compare 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.200.—On the precise meaning of πένομαι, πενία,compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 551 ff. (Cf. πένης, πόνος, πονηρός.) \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8694","accentedUnicode":"πένομαι","shortDef":"be in need","mediumDef":"be in need","stepGloss":"be in need","stepTransliteration":"penomai","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}